goal_descEN: Conserve and sustainably use the oceans, seas and marine resources for sustainable development
target_descEN: By 2020, conserve at least 10 per cent of coastal and marine areas, consistent with national and international law and based on the best available scientific information
indicator_descEN: Coverage of protected areas in relation to marine areas
series_tags: ['marine resources', 'marine ecosystems', 'living marine resources', 'national parks and protected areas', 'oceans', 'biological diversity']
seriesDescription: Average proportion of Marine Key Biodiversity Areas (KBAs) covered by protected areas (%)
sources: BirdLife International, IUCN and UNEP-WCMC (2019). Based on spatial overlap between polygons for Key Biodiversity Areas from the World Database of Key Biodiveristy Areas (www.keybiodiversityareas.org) and polygons for protected areas from the World Database on Protected Areas (www.protectedplanet.net)
